TextBlock.TextLine: desine to be excused, in the like occasion, for itt comes in a vere ill sime
I have sold 3 of yd cloathes more, & shall endeavour to putt of the rest to cleare
al. I receave tust now a letter from JB. by which he sayes that Iohm de coninck doing
hath afslicted him soo much, that he kept his bed well 8 dayes, butt no hopes yett
for any mony. I knw here are more protested bills att his charge, butt what
shall I do to secure you, I wrott him that you sended mee his ledder of 17 past, he
desires to be excused, & that next week he will endeavour to remitt some mony, &
deseres mee not to astront him, butt I feare he will suffer by others, what passes
more you shall know rext
a4 april 1682
London n Deury Maijnard
in the first curtt have pertely answered yd of 13 & 17th past, as for spanish cloather
puk now & then a 3 as you finde our advantidge, butt not to many & most low
prijsen of 6„6„ 7 ƒ & under 8 a gad pray desist not with the 618 silver mack for
I can nott gett 2 dyed & to make them well must have 5 att a time, so haster ther
as much you can, in case you finde apenniewortk in reds send a bale of 5 or 10
butt if to deare, would rather desist. if the pack whites low prijses be good cherp
please to buy 5& of £30- & 5& of £35- a 36 god send klarck specdly over, for
I want the goods on his board, I have understood mr. Randals beeng fouled, & buthes
of Epon & sampson of london, trnly itt is fallen vere heary upon some here ood confort
the concerned: some difference between John de coninck & John vale hath been cause
of severall bills on sV protested, amonghst others 3 of H.C. of which he payd the
finst which was all ready returned in london, the other 2 I have payd to help
my good old freind for this & last time, for though I have effects of his yett they
are standing out debts, so there is no danger, I do for the valew here inclosed send
you my bill on him att Wto £200- p att 35„3, for which please to secoeune
the needfull, & where payd pas to yd. owne acctt. god comfort houest I v. for he
is nu an asslicted condition, to have so many proteste, I have seen non of yd bill
butt I suppose John de Coninck doth discharge them for yd. honor, as you do for him
other wise I should take care for them
a4d
Lenden mr. Edmund Warner
on the 21th past wrort you the needfull, sence recd yd of 13 d with yd dixcethons, for
what laccs you order mee so provide, which will be osserved in all respects I shall
what
eveny weet dispatch one or 2 packetts, & finst all ready I have by mee for yd acctt
which will be cheapes by 15 by what dayly I now buy assureing you, that you have
all advantages in that trade that can be exspected, & in case you do nott finde mee
capable, to incorridge not onely, butt to continew you in the same, then should not
advise you to medele with itt att all, for sur. I know them that buy dearer by
butt itt is the ready mony that fathous the bottom of itt, & a continuall imploy, I am
sure that England never demanded more laces then now butt the woust of all is
that itt is in so many handes, yett pray do nott under valew itt, & be confident of my
endeavour to serve you as well as can be imagined nay I am sure no beddy shall out
do you, except they would wort for others. you define no more Antworp laces, I have
about for £250- bought for you, butt seeng you do not desie itt, itt shall be sendt to
other freinds, yett them of ¼ of an ele are there by, which I have ordered to be made for
you neversheles I have not one & to many neither can wee att this time provide
great quantiies to our minde, so must take the best opportunitie I can, for other wise must take
all as itt comes, & allow the worck wonnen their pleasure, which I do not rekon yd. Intrest: the
is some patt. of smaller flowers, butt not so plentie yett in low prijsed goods, whoever you shall
have of itt, & I shall observe the mannes you direct mee of makeing up the packetts, the f. of
plaine ground N.117, I could not discorer any thing of what you say, in case you can not pust att
oft for proffitt returne itt, & I'll shew itt the maker, sure wee bny not oneell, butt what in
looven: whoever I hope to give you content as much as any one can do
@ 4 april 1682
Londen m. anthus Anneslay
I have delayed answer to yd of 20 feb. last, because I did not thinck butt that
ene now I should have been in a good capacitie to remitt you a good some of mony
butt allthinghs go so cnoss, & ill here, that wee are almost unden, whoeves I have
grasped something for you which shall remitt you & rext, you dechine of continuing the
stuff srade here, patience I can not incorridge you to trade against yd him our
whoever in case I finde some thigh thingh more werth yd notice & proffitt shall
advise you
Brussel Mons Jeon enle
@4 april 16682
Mons. tis mij leet te verstaen bij den ul van 3 deser ul in dispositie
& ongelegentijt, hebbe heden soo veel te wege gebraght dat den brief
an m. collier heden overvallen geprotesteert sijnd niet en is
wegh gesonden maer op gehouden sal worden tot dijnsdagh
soo gelieft die weirde aen mij te besorgen, om den selven
te voldoen, ende de reste sal met meerder gelegen tijdt af
waohten, waer op mij verlaete
russel mons. carsavont
4 april 1682
mons. in antwort aen den ul van gisteren en hebbe present
gene witte engelsche baeyen vollgens ul versock alenelijck
vier stucks van stijf een elle breet tot ƒ26:10 ot kan ick ul
daer op & mede bedienen gelieft te commanderen maer om
dat de selve soo smal sijn en heb die niet derven seyndek
verwachte een groote partije ballen ider dagh te arriveven
alswanneer weveel beter sal versien sijn gelieft ul daer
te gen sil te hebben gelieft maer te commanderen
brussel Ana mari de vos

mainff den 2 deser hebbe aen ul gesonden pr dondaghs bend
tschip op brussel twe pack het een gemerckt a db voor
mj alex ander de bresst van berge ende et ander voor ur gan
batasta. massain mede van borge het welck gewerckt is

brussel monsr. Coots
26 april 1682
monsr. sedort mijnen van 8 deser, den ul van den selven dato bekomen
wat onkosten als andersins wegens het clavers aet gepassceirt is
verwachte heden te verstaen, het pack sergen sien tegemoet
